# Day 2 Review

## Assemblies and Visual Studio
What is your understanding of what is meant by the term "Assembly" in .NET?
    It is a compiled code that consists of CIL (Common Intermediate Language).
What is the relationship between an assembly and visual studio Project?
    The contents of a VS project defines how code is to be compiled, which builds an assembly.
What is a solution in Visual Studio?
    A sort of container that groups multiple related projects and their files.
What are the two types of Assemblies discussed in class?
    Executable (.exe) and Libraries (.dll).
What is the thing that makes an assembly "Runnable" - what is the *entry* point of an Assembly?
    The entry point of an assembly is the main method, such as an .exe file. The main method must be present in one of the classes in order to run.

## What is the "Common Language Runtime (CLR)" 
    CLR is the primary runtime engine of .NET and ensures cross-language interoperability.

## What is "Dotnet Core"? What's that all about?
    A forerunner of what we now know as .NET, Dotnet Core was developed by Microsoft. It was the first to work on platforms beyond just Windows.

## What is the Common Type System (CTS)?
    The type system that all .NET languages share (C#, F#, etc.).

